                <div class="modal-header">
                    <h2 class="modal-title text-primary">About FiRST PiCk Phonics</h2>
                    <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
                </div>

                <div class="modal-body">
                    <h4>Phonics</h4>
                    <p>Phonics is a method for teaching reading and writing to beginners. Phonics teaches
                        the
                        relationship between the sounds of the spoken language and the letters (or groups of
                        letters) of the written language.
                    </p>
                    <h4>Phonics Rules</h4>
                    <p>According to understood.org, about 84% of English words follow the language's
                        soundspelling
                        rules, which are also known as phonics rules. About 50% of words can be spelled
                        accurately using sound-symbol correspondence patterns alone, and another 36% can be
                        spelled accurately except for one speech sound. The remaining 4% of words are
                        considered
                        irregular. These rules can be a helpful tool for beginning readers, struggling
                        readers,
                        and
                        English Language Learners.
                    </p>
                    <h4>The FiRST PiCk Phonics Program</h4>
                    <p>
                        This program is specifically designed for students in rural India between the ages
                        of
                        8-12
                        years, although younger children can also benefit from it. It teaches reading skills
                        by
                        introducing phonics rules sequentially to beginning readers, using words and
                        sentences
                        they are either familiar with or likely to be encountered frequently. All sentences
                        are
                        grounded in the rural Indian context. <br>
                        Reading and comprehension need to go hand in hand. The FiRST PiCk Phonics Program
                        integrates phonics instruction with vocabulary instruction using activities, such as
                        vocabulary cards, songs, poems, stories, dialogs and plays.
                    </p>
                    <h4>Program Designer</h4>
                    <p>
                        A learning designer by profession, Puja created online learning programs for large
                        organizations for over 20 years before moving back to India and settling down in
                        Dharamshala. She has been teaching English speaking and reading in the government
                        Primary Schools in and around Dharamshala since 2014. A design assignment in 2015
                        for
                        an American Teacher Training company got her excited about teaching reading using
                        Phonics. The FiRST PiCk Phonics program is her brainchild, which draws from her
                        extensive
                        knowledge about learning theories and design principles, and last but not the least,
                        her
                        deep love for the children of Rakkar.
                    </p>
                </div>

            </div>
